notes: Bait|Black Pheidole and large Pachycondyla. Video|Met Harry, Dunia and Manuel in Quebrada Grande at 7. Walked up from leaving the 4-Runner at 8:21. Gtraps open and bait out at 9:30. Windy and rainy in the morning, and windy and clear in the afternoon. Temperature around 14C. Photos of sun and cloug. GigaPan taken at the same spot as in December 201. Should be a collembola visible (photo 5287). Spider monkeys around but no notice of me was taken. Video of small myrmicins under gigapan, slow moving adelomyrmex at bait 1, and black pheidole with abundant soldiers at bait 5.|Waypoint 34|IMG_6578.JPG|http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d86_Q2VV1BA|http://gigapan.org/gigapans/71665/|http://bit.ly/eY3FM9|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

Can hear construction below. Traps and bait out at 8:30am. Many stout, red-haired gastered ponerines. Video of them cutting something. P. apicalis seem afraid of them. Video of atta, Video of Strumigenys, Video of Extatoma on branch. 360 GigaPan taken at 3/4 on the trail. Page 125 of book. notes: ActiveSearch|Gnaptogenys (mucho), red Hypoponera, tiny yellow myrmicinae, black myrmicinae|10mEPE|Waypoint 192||Isidro (Caca0o 2009) let me in the locked gate - didn`t recognise me at first. Walked up from 7:45-9:00 to 1200m. Traps open and bait down at 9:33. Very windy rain, and cloud too - 14C. Can feel ground moving as roots are shifted by the wind. Tarp up. Very dominant/common ant was Gnaptogenys - all traps, baits, sifts, searches. Video of Gnapto at Bait 4. 360 GigaPan (17x48) taken at ~Sift 1. Moist. Malaise trap erected at Santa Rosa at 6:30am. Page 132 in book.|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/66885/|http://bit.ly/gJZD7p |http://sites.google.com/site/acgdecembercollections/|

notes: ActiveSearch|Pheidolex2, Hypoponera|8mEPE|Waypoint 181||Dominant taxa here is the small yellow Myrmicinae (Wasmania) with the black spot on the gaster. Everywhere in the hundreds and thousands. This with the unfortunate (?) Solenopsis invicta from Gongora is also here. Video of Pachycondyla apicalis, Wasmania and other insects taken. 360 GigaPan taken in the middle of the stream near station 6. Howler monkeys, blue morphos cicadeas calling and `leopard` frogs. Almost no rain. On Page 127 of book. |http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/66821/|http://bit.ly/ewci2R|http://sites.google.com/site/acgdecembercollections/|

notes: Winkler||Met Harry, Dunia and Manuel in Quebrada Grande at 7. Walked up from leaving the 4-Runner at 8:21. Gtraps open and bait out at 9:30. Windy and rainy in the morning, and windy and clear in the afternoon. Temperature around 14C. Photos of sun and cloug. GigaPan taken at the same spot as in December 201. Should be a collembola visible (photo 5287). Spider monkeys around but no notice of me was taken. Video of small myrmicins under gigapan, slow moving adelomyrmex at bait 1, and black pheidole with abundant soldiers at bait 5.|Waypoint 34|IMG_6578.JPG||http://gigapan.org/gigapans/71665/|http://bit.ly/eY3FM9|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

Video of Gnapto at Bait 4. 360 GigaPan (17x48) taken at ~Sift 1. Moist. Malaise trap erected at Santa Rosa at 6:30am. notes: Winkler|Poneromorph and myrmicinae|10mEPE|Waypoint 192||Isidro (Caca0o 2009) let me in the locked gate - didn`t recognise me at first. Walked up from 7:45-9:00 to 1200m. Traps open and bait down at 9:33. Very windy rain, and cloud too - 14C. Can feel ground moving as roots are shifted by the wind. Tarp up. Very dominant/common ant was Gnaptogenys - all traps, baits, sifts, searches. Video of Gnapto at Bait 4. 360 GigaPan (17x48) taken at ~Sift 1. Moist. Malaise trap erected at Santa Rosa at 6:30am.
